{
  "texts": [
    "(1) To intimidate or to warn the predator by the display of size, colors, ornaments, noises, fearless behavior, and.",
    "(2) To educate, or make their visual, olfactory, audible, and behavioral signals remembered by the predator.",
    "Some of these signals are naturally weapons in themselves, such as a large body, antlers, big canines, venomous spike, or an aggressive behavior, referred to as intrinsic aposematic signals (Alonso and Jordania, 2023).",
    "Other aposematic signals, such as body odor or colors, or loud noise, which are not themselves harmful, can be categorized as semantic aposematic signals.",
    "Although both categories qualify as aposematic signals, the latter is the true meaning of aposematism."
  ]
}